I"p<p>Axis angle을 Quaternion으로 변환해보자 ! <br /></p>

<h2 id="수식">수식</h2>

\[\begin{align}
&amp; qx = ax \; sin(\frac{angle}{2}) \\
&amp; qy = ay \; sin(\frac{angle}{2}) \\
&amp; qz = az \; sin(\frac{angle}{2}) \\
&amp; qw = con(\frac{angle}{2}) \\
\end{align}\]

<p><br /><br /></p>

<p>\(where, \\\) <br />
  1) the axis is normalized:  \(ax^2 + ay^2 + az^2 = 1  \\\) <br />
  2) the quaternion is also normalized : \(qw^2 + qx^2 + qy^2+qz^2=1 \\ cos(\frac{angle}{2})^2 + ax^2 \; sin(\frac{angle}{2})^2 + ay^2 \; sin(\frac{angle}{2})^2+ az^2 \; sin(\frac{angle}{2})^2 = 1 \\\) <br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

